link:labelLink.link:label: Category Of Exposure Dimension
This dimension is used to segment data reported based on the categories of exposures.
Category Of Exposure Collateral Guarantee Dimension

This dimension is used to segment data based on the categories of the eligible collateral or guarantee replacing the underlying asset exposure. The categories of exposures are determined in accordance with relevant prudential standards.
Reinsurance
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as reinsurance.
Life Insurance Policy By Related Party
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as a life insurance policy issued by a registered life company which is a related entity.
Bank Bills
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as bank bills.
Policy Reinsurer OS Bus

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as an approved reinsurance arrangement in respect of overseas business, with a related entity of a registered life company that has a specialist reinsurer statutory fund.
Bank Bills Assets Guaranteed OS Govt

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as bank bills or an Assets guaranteed by an overseas provincial government (equivalent in status to an Australian State government), in the country in whose currency the liabilities of a fund are denominated.
Reinsurance Arrangement

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as a reinsurance arrangement with a registered life company that is not a related entity of the life company; or with APRA's written approval, a reinsurance arrangement in respect of overseas business, with a related entity of a registered life company that has a fund which is a specialist reinsurer.
Security Loan Reinsure G 1 To 3 Real Estate Income Producing Property

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as any other actively traded security; or non-traded security, loan, or reinsurance arrangement with counterparty grade of 1, 2 or 3; or real estate; or other income producing real property asset.
Other Actively Traded Security
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as any other actively traded security.
Policy Special Reinsure Grade 1 To 3 Agreement Time
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as reinsurance with approved retrocessionaires with counterparty grade of 1, 2 or 3 at the time of agreement (Specialist reinsurers only).
Other Exposure
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as any asset not covered by the list.
Non Reinsurance
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as non-reinsurance.
Guaranteed Currency Provincial Government

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as an asset guaranteed by an overseas provincial government (equivalent in status to an Australian State government), being a government in the country in whose currency the liabilities of the statutory fund are denominated.
Combination Multiple Exposures
The information reported relates to a combination of multiple categories of exposures.
Guaranteed By Government

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as assets guaranteed by Australian State or Federal government or by national government of the country in whose currency the liabilities of the fund are denominated.
Property
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as real estate or other income producing real property asset.
Outstanding Premiums
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as outstanding premiums receivable by a reinsurer under a reinsurance policy with a registered life company.
Non Traded Sec Loan Reinsurance
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as non-traded security, loan or reinsurance arrangement with a counterparty grade of 1, 2 or 3.
Policy Special Reinsure Grade 1 To 3
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as reinsurance with approved retrocessionaires with current counterparty grade of 1, 2 or 3 (Specialist reinsurers only).
Policy Non Related
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as reinsurance arrangement with non-related registered life company.
Deposits
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as deposits.
Self Securitised Assets

The information reported relates to securities held as a result of internal securitisation, also referred to as self-securitisation. This process is where an originator sells a pool of assets to a related special purpose vehicle (SPV), and the SPV in turn issues debt securities, which are held entirely by the originator.
Foreign Sovereigns
The information required relates to exposures to non-Australian Sovereigns.
Foreign Government
The information reported relates to any exposures to foreign government.
Not Self Issued Securitised Assets
The information reported relates to securitised assets that have not been issued by the actual entity.
Other Debt Issued Securities
The information reported relates to other debt issued securities not reported elsewhere.
Supranational
The information reported relates to exposure to supranational.
Asset Backed Securities
The information reported relates to a financial security backed by a loan, lease or receivables against assets.
Public Sector Entities

The information reported relates to exposures to all public sector units controlled by state / territory governments are classified to the State / Territory Level of Government. For the purposes of the classification include: -Government units controlled by a state / territory government -Public financial corporations controlled by a state / territory government -Public non-financial corporations controlled by a state / territory government.
Corporate Securities
The information reported relates to other securities issued by corporations.
Public Sector Entity Or Multilateral Development Bank
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as assets issued or guaranteed by Public Sector Entity (PSEs) or multilateral development banks (MDBs).
Asset Backed Commercial Paper Asset Backed Securities Covered Bonds And Other Structured Financing
The information reported relates to secured funding through Asset Backed Commercial Paper, Asset Backed Securities, covered bonds and other structured financing SPVs (Special Purpose Vehicles).
Australian And Foreign Sovereign Government Guaranteed
The information reported relates to exposures in securities guaranteed by Australian government and foreign sovereign government.
Debt Security
The reported information relates to debt securities including bank bills and Certificate of Deposits (CDs).
Authorised Deposit Taking Institution Issued Securities
The information reported relates to authorised deposit-taking institutions (ADI) issued securities.
Supranationals And Foreign Government
The information reported relates to exposure to supranationals plus foreign government issued securities.
Euro Commercial Paper
The information reported relates to exposure to an unsecured, short-term debt issued by a bank or corporation in offshore markets other than the USA.
US Commercial Paper
The information reported relates to exposure to an unsecured, short-term debt issued by a bank or corporation in the USA market.
Bank For International Settlement International Monetary Fund European Central Bank European Community Multilateral Development Banks

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as assets issued or guaranteed by Bank for International Settlement (BIS), International Monetary Fund (IMF), European Central Bank (ECB), and European Community (EC) or multilateral development banks (MDBs).
Supranational Plus Foreign Government Issued And Australian And Foreign Government Guaranteed
The information reported relates to exposure to supranational plus foreign government issued securities and Australian and foreign government guaranteed securities.
Sovereign Central Bank
The information reported relates to any exposure to assets issued or guaranteed by a Central Bank or Sovereign.
Central Banks
The information reported relates to any exposures to or guarantees by central banks.
Asset Backed Commercial Paper

The information reported relates to a short-term investment vehicle with a maturity that is typically between 90 and 180 days. The security itself is typically issued by a bank or other financial institution. The notes are backed by physical assets such as trade receivables, and are generally used for short-term financing needs.
Other Private Securities
The information reported relates to other private securities not already reported.
Guaranteed By Australian Government
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as assets guaranteed by Australian government.
Guaranteed By Non Australian Sovereigns
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as assets guaranteed by non Australian government/sovereigns.
Superannuation Deposits That Meets Operational Deposits
The information reported relates to exposures categorised superannuation fund deposits that meets the definition of operational deposits.
Liquidity Intermediated Deposits

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as all intermediated deposits for liquidity purposes when you look through to the original transaction as per Prudential Standard APS 210 - Liquidity, Attachment A.
Non Superannuation Deposits Do Not Meet Operational Deposits
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as non-superannuation fund deposits that meet the definition of operational deposits.
RMBS
The information reported relates to exposures in stock that are residential mortgage-backed securities (RMBS).
Other RBA Repo Eligible Securities
The information reported relates to exposures in any other Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) repo-eligible debt security other than high quality liquid asset (HQLA) - HQLA1, HQLA2A and HQLA2B.
Common Share Equity
The information reported relates to any exposures to common share equity (ordinary shares).
Certificates Of Deposit Bank Bills Other Short Term Debt Securities
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as certificates of deposit, bank bills, other short-term debt securities.
Other Offshore Central Bank Repo Eligible Securities
The information reported relates to exposures in any other offshore central repo-eligible debt security other than high quality liquid asset (HQLA) - HQLA1, HQLA2B and/or HQLA2B.
Australian State Government Or Territory Central Borrowing Authorities
The information reported relates to any exposures to Australian State Government or territory central borrowing authorities.
Superannuation Fund Deposits
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as superannuation fund deposits.
Australian Government
The information reported relates to any exposures to Australian Government debt securities.
Non Superannuation Fund Deposits
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as non-superannuation fund deposits.
Non RMBS
The information reported relates to exposures in stock that are non-residential mortgage-backed securities (non-RMBS).
Bank Bills Commercial Paper And Other Non Deposit Obligations
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as bank bills, commercial paper and other non-deposit obligations.
Loans

The information reported is in relation to loans. Loans means a financial asset that is: (1) created when a creditor lends funds directly to a debtor; and (2) is evidenced by non-negotiable documents.
Hybrid Securities
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as hybrid securities which are securities that combine elements of debt securities and equity securities.
Members Withdrawable Shares
The information reported are borrowings classified as members' withdrawable shares.
Preference Shares
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as preference shares which are type of equity security that has a priority over dividend payments and to the assets of the company.
Finance Leases
A lease that transfers substantially all the risks and rewards incidental to the ownership of the asset. Title may or may not eventually be transferred.
Other Financial Institutions Securities
The information reported relates to exposures to counterparties classified as other financial institutions which are any financial institutions not already reported.
Securities Other Interest Earning Assets
The information reported is in relation to securities and other interest earning assets that are not loans or finance leases.
Finance Leases Bill Acceptances

The reported information relates to finance leases and bill acceptances. Finance leases are leases that transfers substantially all the risks and rewards incidental to the ownership of the asset. Title may or may not eventually be transferred. Bill acceptances are bills of exchange that have been signed by the drawee, which 'accepts' liability to pay out the funds on the due date. The drawer incurs a corresponding liability towards the drawee.
Non Financial Corporates Securities
The information reported relates to exposures to non financial Corporates whose main activity is producing goods or non-financial services for sale at market prices.
Non Bank Authorised Deposit Taking Institution Securities

The information reported relates to exposures to a body corporate authorised under subsection 9(3) of the Banking Act 1959 to carry on banking business in Australia, but which does not hold a consent under section 66 of the Banking Act 1959 to use the word 'bank'.
Semi Government Securities

The information reported relates to exposures classified as Semi Government which are debt obligations of a central borrowing authority of a state or territory of the Commonwealth of Australia. It includes fixed-interest rate bonds, linked bonds and Treasury notes issued by a state or territory of the Commonwealth of Australia.
Negotiable Certificate Of Deposit

The information report relates to a negotiable certificate of deposit which are negotiable-bearer debt securities. They are issued at a discount to the face value, can be traded in the secondary market and do not require endorsement when sold. Include transferable certificates of deposit.
Debt Securities Not Non Negotiable Certificates Of Deposit

The information reported relates to debt securities excluding non-negotiable certificates of deposit (CDs). These are transferable instruments evidencing a relationship of indebtedness. They are characterised by having a definable return that is not based on the economic performance of the issuing entity. This includes negotiable (CDs), bills of exchange, and hybrid securities treated as liabilities under Australian Accounting Standards.
Bills Of Exchange Bank Accepted

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as bank accepted bills of exchange. These are bills of exchange that have been signed by the bank, which 'accepts' liability to pay out the funds on the due date. The drawer incurs a corresponding liability towards the bank.
Bills Of Exchange Not Bank Accepted
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as bills of exchange that are not bank accepted.
Debt Securities Not Bills Of Exchange
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as debt securities other than bills of exchange.
Commercial Paper

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as commercial paper which is a written promise to pay a specified sum of money to the bearer at an agreed date. It is usually issued for terms ranging from 30 to 180 days and is sold to an investor at a discount to the face value.
Loans And Finance Leases

The information reported is in relation to loans and finance leases. Loans are financial assets that are: (1) created when a creditor lends funds directly to a debtor; and (2) are evidenced by non-negotiable documents. Finance leases are leases that transfer substantially all the risks and rewards incidental to the ownership of the asset. Title may or may not eventually be transferred.
Covered Bond

The information reported relates to covered bonds that are bonds, notes or other debentures issued by an authorised deposit-taking institution (ADI), liabilities to the holders of which, or their representatives, are recoverable from the ADI and secured by assets beneficially owned by a covered bond special purpose vehicle.
Bills Of Exchange

A bill of exchange is an unconditional order in writing, addressed by one person to another, signed by the person giving it (the drawer), requiring the person to whom it is addressed (the drawee or acceptor) to pay on demand, or at a fixed or determinable future time, a sum of money to, or to the order of, a specified party, or to bearer. This is defined in the Bills of Exchange Act 1909.
Debt Securities Not Bills Of Exchange Not Negotiable Certificates Of Deposit
The information reported relates to debt securities other than bills of exchange or negotiable certificates of deposit.
Loans Finance Leases Bill Acceptances

The reported information relates to business finance which covers loans, finance leases and bill acceptances. Finance leases are leases that transfers substantially all the risks and rewards incidental to the ownership of the asset. Title may or may not eventually be transferred.Bill acceptances are bills of exchange that have been signed by the drawee, which 'accepts' liability to pay out the funds on the due date. The drawer incurs a corresponding liability towards the drawee. Loans are financial assets that are: (1) created when a creditor lends funds directly to a debtor; and (2) are evidenced by non-negotiable documents.
Senior Unsecured Debt

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as any unsecured debt security that must be repaid ahead of all other unsecured and subordinated debt security holders other than those outlined in section 13A(3)(a)-(e) of the Banking Act 1959 in the event that the authorised deposit-taking institution is unable to meet its obligations or is about to suspend payment.
Other Interest Bearing Liabilities
The information reported relates to interest-bearing liabilities other than deposits and debt securities.
Tier 2 Capital Instruments

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as instruments that are compliant with the definition of Tier 2 capital in Prudential Standard APS 111 Capital Adequacy: Measurement of Capital (APS 111).
Additional Tier 1 Capital Instruments
The information reported relates to exposures categorised as Additional Tier 1 Capital in Prudential Standard APS 111 Capital Adequacy: Measurement of Capital (APS 111).
Other Hybrid Securities And Subordinated Debt

The information reported relates to exposures categorised as other hybrid securities treated as liabilities and subordinated debt that are not classified as negotiable certificates of deposit; covered bonds; senior unsecured debt; additional Tier 1 capital instruments; or Tier 2 capital instruments.
Loans And Advances
Loans and advances are those financial assets categorised as "Loans and Receivables" in the accounting standards, other than "Trade Receivables" and "Cash".
Market Related
Exposures arising from market related contracts.
Other Not Loans And Advances
The exposure is relating to exposures other than to loans and advances.
Not Market Related
Exposures that are not arising from market related contracts.
Commercial Real Estate
The information reported relates to loans and finance leases for commercial property exposures as defined in Reporting Standard ARS 230.0 - Commercial Property.
